        "Dream.Org excels in organizational governance and financial transparency. They maintain an <cite id=\"7\">85% independent board</cite>, ensuring strong oversight of their mission-driven activities. Their financial health is bolstered by <cite id=\"7\">4.8 months of working capital</cite>, providing a stable foundation for long-term advocacy campaigns. Furthermore, the organization has demonstrated a commitment to learning by <cite id=\"7\">sharing information about their feedback practices</cite> through Candid, showing a willingness to adapt based on community and donor input."
      ],
      "summary": "Dream.Org operates at the intersection of criminal justice reform and environmental equity, aiming to close prison doors while opening opportunities in the green economy. The organization reported <cite id=\"8\">total revenue of $4,091,131</cite> in 2023, focusing its efforts on bridging racial and partisan divides to achieve systemic change. With an <cite id=\"7\">overall score of 97.97.75/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>, the charity demonstrates a high level of institutional maturity and transparency. Their work is structured through several key initiatives, including the <cite id=\"1\">Green, Justice, and Tech programs</cite>, which advocate for policy shifts and community empowerment. A significant portion of their recent activity involved large-scale grantmaking, including <cite id=\"8\">$54,319,186 in total grants</cite> distributed to domestic partners. While the organization maintains a <cite id=\"7\">perfect 97/100 score in Accountability & Finance</cite> from third-party evaluators, its financial model shifted significantly in 2023, with <cite id=\"8\">spending exceeding revenue</cite> as it utilized existing reserves for major program expansions. This strategy allows for high-impact advocacy, such as targeting <cite id=\"2\">federal funding for environmental justice</cite>, though it results in a high <cite id=\"7\">cost per beneficiary of approximately $17,806</cite> due to the resource-heavy nature of legislative and systemic reform.",
